[OC] Sanders Diederich.

Commonly known as Sandy, is a breed of Vanguine. (generally speaking, he's a vampire). His physical appearance is just like a normal human, but with slight differences. He has two pairs of fangs, two fangs on top and two on the bottom, all of which are partially concealed, but extended when opening the mouth. He has light complexion, pale, and blue veins can sometimes be seen from under his skin. He has gray eyes, thick eyebrows, and hair of the same color.

He is 185-190 cm tall and 80-90 kg.

As a Vanguine, Sandy regularly drinks blood as a nourishment. He prefers deer or horse's blood. Occasionally he enjoys the blood of any other breeds, but never kills them. He also enjoys cooked meal.

Sandy has quick reflexes and is capable of doing action faster than human. He has higher resistance to heat and cold. When injured, he can slowly regenerate health, which can be hastened by drinking blood.

Sandy's preferred weapon is a steak knife. His battle strategy consists of slashing the enemy while running, throwing punches and kicks, and stabbing.

Done in A4 sketchbook with pencil and pens.

[OC] Redara Schneider.

This is an oc of my never-be-published book. And NO, she's not a rooster hybrid or something like that.

Redara is a breed of Diarral. (generally speaking, she is half-owl). She has dark complexion, thick black hair, and a pair of double-lidded hazel eyes. She is strong built. Her wingspan is twice her height, grayish with black dots, and decorated with a pair of horns. She has talons for feet, a pair that is incredibly sharp and strong. She is capable of lifting something or someone three times her weight.

She is 165 cm tall, and weight about 65-70 kg, 140 kg with wings included.

Her battle strategy consists of scattering the enemy's formation, throwing fire and rock from above, impaling the enemy using her wings or talons, and smacking the enemy in the face.

Redara's armor covers her vital parts, but leaving open space for her wings. She has double-lidded eyes, the first clear lids protect her in flight, while the second lids act just like a normal human's eyelids.

I'm currently trying to re-develop the story, as it has been a long time since i first wrote the draft.

No stealing please. Done in A4 sketchbook with pencil and drawing pens.

Shiawase Kissa Sanchoume.

It has been yeaaars since the manga ended, but i still can't move on from the story. It has the best plot and comedy, the best characters that can make you go 'aww' and the best advice to stay happy.

Here on the top we have Matsumoto Nankichi, the manager of the cafe and the step-father of Satsuki Shindou. Matsumoto is rather easy going, always getting bullied, and is young in the soul. He also suffers from bad joints.

Right below him is Nishikawa Ichirou. He's the 18 year-old genius who falls asleep when hungry, and wakes up when his mouth is filled with food. He's actually rich af, and constantly has poker face.

The dark-haired guy below him is Satsuki Shindou, the 20 year-old 'Demon King' who always sulks and rarely smiles. Has the tendency to be violent, yet patient at the same time. Extremely shy to his own feeling.

Lastly we have Takamura Uru, or Uru-chan! She's the 16 year-old sunshine with the heart of gold. She inherits her father's unbelievable strength, capable of lifting a grown man, but she will always have the body of an elementary school kid.

Done in A4 sketchbook with 2B pencil and some drawing pens.

Meet The Robins.

Lately Sieg has been telling me about Batman's family. So here they are:

1. Richard Grayson (bottom left). He's the first Robin, used to perform in circus with his family until they were killed, and he was taken by Bruce Wayne. When he 'graduated' he became Nightwing. He's kinda cheerful, and he also acts as the oldest 'brother' in the family.

2. Jason Todd (top right). Remember in Suicide Squad, Harley Quinn's introduction said that she assisted in killing Robin? Well, here you go. Jason is famously known for his death caused by Joker and Harley Quinn, and eventually came back as Red Hood. He's cynical, and willing to kill. Still blaming Batman for his death tho... 3. Tim Drake (top left). The most tactical Robin that even Batman admires him. Tim is the calm son in the family, and unlike any other Robins, he still had both parents when he took the mantle of Robin. He 'graduated' and became Red Robin.

4. Damian Wayne (bottom right). The son of Bruce Wayne and Talia Al-Ghul, and was raised and trained to be an assassin. At age 10, he was sent to Batman by Talia to disrupt his work, but eventually aids him as Robin. Despite being a hard-headed kid, Damian is powerful and highly skilled in combat. Like Jason, he is willing to kill, something that Batman disagrees. In Injustice, Damian is responsible for accidentally killing Dick Grayson (Nightwing). Done in A4 Sketchbook with 2B pencil and some drawing pens.
